->fs tt
@node tt "Tooltypes / ARexx port"
Cheater understands the following tooltypes:

PROJECTS (without parameters) Project list is shown at start

BUFMEMSIZE=     Size of buffer memory PER PROJECT

Number of memorized addresses = buffer mem / 4
(100000 Bytes => 25000 addresses)

       DOC=     Name and path of the documentation for online help

  KEYFILE=      Name and path of the keyfile (Default 'Cheater.key'
                                                  and 'S:Cheater.key')

The same keywords can be used from CLI:
Cheater: BUFMEMSIZE/N,PROJECTS/S,DOC,KEYFILE


ARexx commands:  (Port: 'CHEATER')

SET   does the same as the 'Set'-Button

Use: Can be sent by for example MCP, FKeys or Toolmanager via hotkey.
     So you can change values while you are playing.
     Great idea, Mucho !!!  :-)
